</mei>
<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- M1-2 (G D7): alternating ①/⑤7 — open LH G2-D3-G3-B3 and D2-A2-F#3-C4
- M3-4 (D Am7 D): Am7 with extended bass A2-E3-G3-C4
- M4 (D): full "333" A4-C#5-E5 RH — momentary richness
- M7 (G Em Am D7): all 4 chords in measure — most active bar so far
- M8/M16/M24: ① full "334" holds with G1 pedal — 3 structural arrivals
- M9-10 (G#°7 = ⑦°): F#° diatonic sub — F#2-C3-A3-E3 creates strong dissonance
- M11-12: ②/④ chromatic center of hymn — Am "333" E5
- M13: ②7/⑤7 double dominant preparation for M14
- M17-24: Stanza 3 — same harmonic plan but fresh inversions:
  M18: ①¹ "43", M20: ⑤² 2nd inv, M21: ④ quartal "44" F5

VOICE LEADING:
- M7 to M8: D2→G1 bass step; inner voice F#→G (leading tone resolves)
- M9: ⑦° F# creates tension — resolves to Am M9 beat 3, then to ⑥ Em M10
- M23→24: Full four-chord cadence with all voices at maximum voicing → final ①

TEXTURE ARC:
- M1-8: Stanza 1 — moderate, building to ①"334" at M8
- M9-16: Stanza 2 — adventurous, ⑦° chromatic, ②7/⑤7 double dom
- M17-24: Stanza 3 (repeat) — richest, widest voicings, G5 in RH, G1 pedal final
-->
